p.content:
DZ East

Level 01 - 09

The Decontamination Zones, colloquially known as the Dark Zones, are dangerous areas. Civilians are advised to avoid them at all costs. Aside from the usual presence of armed combatants, there have also been reports of Division agents exploiting the absence of surveillance to turn on their fellow agents.

DZ South

Level 01 - 09

The Decontamination Zones, colloquially known as the Dark Zones, are dangerous areas. Civilians are advised to avoid them at all costs. Aside from the usual presence of armed combatants, there have also been reports of Division agents exploiting the absence of surveillance to turn on their fellow agents.

DZ West

Level 01 - 09

The Decontamination Zones, colloquially known as the Dark Zones, are dangerous areas. Civilians are advised to avoid them at all costs. Aside from the usual presence of armed combatants, there have also been reports of Division agents exploiting the absence of surveillance to turn on their fellow agents.

Control Point

Toxic Alley

The sewage water here is nearly toxic as the Hyenas who ravaged this abandoned construction site.

Control Point

The Vault

A Unite DC protest spilled into violence near this bank, marking a turning point in civil unrest as Green Poison swept unchecked through poorer parts of the city..

Control Point

Fallen Cranes

Sits on what was previously an important supply route. A gang of opportunistic thugs - later part of the Hyenas - used explosives to topple the cranes and ambush a convoy.

Control Point

MLK Memorial Library

A small church community sought refuge here but the Hyenas rammed the building with a burning car then laid siege to the survivors.

Control Point

Demolition Site

A half-destroyed office block, moments from the main Unite DC protest site, that was briefly used by Hyenas for wild debauchery and violent excess.

Control Point

Red Dragon

In the chaotic aftermath of Black Friday, ruthless looters used this location in Chinatown to hoard their ill-gotten gains.

Control Point

Hotel Infirmary

CERA staff did their best in the face of overwhelming odds, but their medical supplies often ended up in the hands of remorseless looters rather then the needy.

Control Point

The Cinderblock

With emergency services stretched beyond breaking point, this was the last line of defense against raging fires. It failed.

Control Point

Navy Plaza

A blood-soaked no man's land created during a long engagement between Hyenas and True Sons as they jostled for dominance, neither one managing to get the edge.

Control Point

Crash Site

The final resting place of the presidential plane, having been taken down by unknown forces.

Control Point

Solar Farm

Forward-thinking JTF engineers established large solar panels here. Most did not live to reap the rewards of their labor, and now multiple hostile forces jostle to take the advantage.

Control Point

No Hope Hotel

Hyenas rampaged through this hotel trying to live out a childish rock star fantasy. Now it stands only as a testament to their mindless violence.

Control Point

Sinkhole

A natural disaster hit the JTF hard at this location on the famous East Mall, just as they were struggling to contain an unnatural one.

Only available after completing the overlapping SHD Side Mission.

Control Point

The Choke

A rapidly-built JTF checkpoint which, at best, struggled to deal with the massive volume of traffic trying to flee DC and the Green Poison. Later used by True sons to besiege the Castle.

Control Point

Metro Ruins

The ceiling of Manning Station collapsed while JTF were digging mass graves for victims of Green Poison.

Control Point

Washington Monument

An iconic beacon of hope that still stands tall despite constant threat from hostile forces.

Control Point

Ellipse Fuel Depot

In a post-crisis world, fuel is nearly as important as water.

Control Point

Flood Levee

Washington saw severe floods at the best of times, and after federal oversight was just a memory, improvised levees such as this one were all that could be managed.

Control Point

The Mast

The comms relay is beyond repair but this abandoned military site still holds significant tactical value.

Control Point

The Nest

Federal employees established sniper nests on top of this building and held out as long as they could, but were overwhelmed by JTF traitors who would eventually join Ridgeway's True Sons.

Control Point

Ivy Tunnel

Nature has already started to reclaim our world, piece by piece, and this eerily quiet underpass is no exception.

Control Point

Navy Hill

Boasts strong defensive qualities such as an elevated position and protection on all sides.

Control Point

Taxi Graveyard

Hostiles have established a defensive perimeter here in an attempt to expand their territory.

Control Point

The World's End

Hundreds of Washington University students gathered here, on campus, to laugh in the face of chaos and death for one final drunken night. If you remember the End of the World party, you weren't there.

Control Point

Sleeping Giant

A stack of empty shipping containers, arranged as improvised high ground by Outcasts seeking to control the border of their territory.

Control Point

Overgrowth

A wild profusion of both graffiti and flora have transformed this intersection. It has long sight lines in multiple directions, giving controllers a strong tactical advantage.

Control Point

Riverside Gas Station

An abandoned gas station with crucial access to the Potomac. The pumps here are long since drained by desperate civilians trying to flee the city, then Outcasts looking to fuel their flames of vengeance.

Control Point

New Venice

An abandoned construction site in a strategically valuable location, and featuring a large pool of sewage overflow.

Control Point

Haunted House

Reputedly one of the most haunted buildings in America before Green Poison changed the world forever. Who knows how many tormented souls wander these halls now.
